	<title>Unselfish Altruism in Nature</title>

	<category term="Altruism" />
	<category term="Genetics" />
	<category term="Morality" />
	<category term="Politics" />
	<category term="Psychology" />

	<content type="xhtml">
		<div xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
			<div class="quote">
				<blockquote cite="http://scienceblogs.com/gregladen/2009/09/acting_for_the_survival_of_the.php">
					<p>
						The bottom line is this: A variant of a gene (an &#8220;allele&#8221;) that confers a trait that results in group-level or species-level survival or reproduction at the expense of the individual will have lower fitness than an allele that instead confers a trait that results in individual survival or reproduction.
					</p>
				</blockquote>
				<p class="quote-by">
					-- <a rel="nofollow" href="http://scienceblogs.com/gregladen/">Greg Laden</a>
				</p>
				<p class="quote-from">
					from "<a rel="nofollow" href="http://scienceblogs.com/gregladen/2009/09/acting_for_the_survival_of_the.php">Acting for the survival of the species (a falsehood)</a>"
				</p>
